latestIgtvVideos.title: Skincare Goals!🌸
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Hey you all!! Hope you guys doing well at your homes during lockdown within your families 💯

So today I'm gonna share with you guys my weekly or twice a week mandatory skin care routine to keep my skin healthy and glowing🤩with use of all home-made products

Process 1: Scrub for Exfoliation

Steps: Take some powder scrub of any brand of your choice. I took my favourite @mcaffeineofficial body scrub which is so good, I use it for my face as well. Then put some drops of honey into it. Mix them well and here's your face scrub is ready. Apply it all over your face and let it become dry for about 10 minutes. And after getting dry, start removing it from your face by massaging in small circular motions. 

Benefits: It will remove all your dead-skin and will make your skin become smooth after scrubbing

Pro Tip: You can use any scrub be it powder or a ready made scrub paste available in market of your choice according to your skin type

Process 2: FacePack for After glow, de-tanning, Flawless finish

Steps: Take 2 tbsp Gram flour(Besan) out of your kitchen and a pinch of turmeric available at your home, add some rose water or if you don't have that u can add plane distilled water. Then add some aloe vera gel into the mixture. Like I have added Aloe vera from a aloe gel tube and also added it through the plant available at my home. It works wonders for your skin. Mix all these ingredients thoroughly and you will get a paste consistency. 
Use a flat face pack brush and apply this paste all over your face and your neck. Keep it for 15-20 minutes until it becomes dry and flaky. Now use a wet tissue and start removing this face pack from your face. And Tada!! Have a flawless, bright and glowy skin in minutes 🌻
 
Pro-tip: Don't speak while you have applied a face pack for it will help you in inviting an unwanted wrinkles to your face as it creates patches while you speak at that time.

Process 3(Optional): Spray some rose water all over your face and neck. Rose water is something I can't live without so I use it daily so many times before my moisturization. It acts as natural toner and helps making your skin toned and refreshing.
 #skincaregoal #skincarereview
